artists.name: All Strings Attached
artists.summary: Call them what you will - high energy Celtic punk, unpredictable gypsy strings, pirate shanty folk rock or a circus sideshow extravaganza; the list of genres used to describe All Strings Attached is endless.  Soaring Eastern-European violin melodies fused with hip-shaking rhythms, driving guitar riffs and layered vocals, All Strings Attached may be hard to describe but they are sure to leave you satisfied

artists.name: Cat and Clint
artists.summary: Cat and Clint have charmed many an audience with their take on Old Time Mountain Music featuring foot-stomping fiddle tunes, haunting ballads, twanging banjo and vintage country blues. They hail from Blackwood, in the Central Highlands of Victoria, one of the Old Time Bluegrass Hotspots of Australia

artists.name: Claire Anne Taylor
artists.summary: Hailing from Tasmania's ancient Tarkine rainforest, Claire Anne Taylor crafts soulful folk songs that capture both the beautiful and dark elements of the human experience. With a colossal voice and a powerfully captivating stage presence, her live shows leave audiences in no doubt they have just witnessed something extraordinary.

artists.name: Dana Sipos
artists.summary: Dana Sipos is an acclaimed Canadian songwriter's songwriter. "Delicate, slightly strange and completely mesmerizing (Gold Flake Paint UK)," Dana tours extensively throughout North America and Europe. Her new album, Trick of the Light, released on Roaring Girl Records in May 2018, is described as a "luminous and compelling work (Exclaim!)."

artists.name: Dean Haitani
artists.summary:
Dean Haitani is a blues & roots singer/songwriter. dean has honed the craft of both acoustic & electric guitar, vocals & harmonica. his music is contemporary, forever pushing the musical envelope, his stories are from his heart & mind with compassion for humanity.
Dean's many successes include touring US, Europe, Australia.

artists.name: Eddie Cole
artists.summary: Soulful vocals, exquisite guitar work set against a solid back beat stomp box, Eddie Cole sings gorgeous originals such as 'Rusty Shack' as well as a selection of choice covers such as 'To make you feel my love' and 'Four five seconds'.

artists.name: Enda Kenny
artists.summary: One of Australia's best known songwriters and a cracking entertainer. Eight countries in the last two years. Eight independent CDs.

artists.name: Forgotten Land
artists.summary: Forgotten Land is a husband and wife duo. Gem tells stories through song and takes you on a journey through her life spent largely in City of Bath in the UK. They moved to Australia finally settling in the beautiful Yackandandah. Gem sings from the heart with emotion and Dave accompanies her with his funky rhythms on percussion including djembe and cajon.

artists.name: Fred Smith Band
artists.summary: Fred Smith joins forces with joins forces with Matt Nightingale on double bass and legendary sideman Carl Pannuzzo to present songs from his rich back catalogue and his new album "Great“ a wry interrogation of American politics, history and pathologies. "a wonderful album" insightful, poetic and often personal"Great" is his best yet.

artists.name: Genevieve Chadwick
artists.summary: Imagine if Janis Joplin and John Lee Hooker had a baby together; musically, this girl would be the offspring of that union. She looks like an angel roars like a lion and plays guitar like a demon.

artists.name: Gordon Mullen
artists.summary: I will accompany myself  on my Kurzweil, Ukulele and guitar. I use my own material supplemented with an original take on popular covers.

artists.name: Grooveyard Hammond Combo
artists.summary: Grooveyard Hammond Combo is a 4 piece organ combo  that plays an extensive and eclectic mix of blues, soul and RnB based tunes. They produce spontaneous, engaging and entertaining music. They have the ability to play completely acoustic using uke's and accordion.

artists.name: Hello Tut Tut
artists.summary: Hello Tut Tut takes its audience on a musical journey shaped by the aesthetics of cultures from around the world. Their debut album World Music Dance Band pays homage to its members ancestry, drawing upon sounds of the klezmer, balkan and gypsy musical traditions in order to craft original music that is both current and timeless.

artists.name: Joel Havea
artists.summary: Joel Havea is soulful singer-songwriter whose many influences reflect his roots as a true world citizen, born in Tonga, raised in Melbourne and currently based in Europe. Since the release of his debut-album in 2012, he has played 600+ concerts in over 20 countries on 4 continents.

artists.name: Leah Jeskie
artists.summary: Leah Jeskie is a singer-songwriter and multi-instrumentalist from North Eastern Victoria. Weaving experiences and stories with eclectic music styles, Leah creates songs that engage your heart and mind. She will be joined by members of the Wood Street Family Band.

artists.name: Luke Robinson
artists.summary: With carefully-crafted lyrics and a powerful bass voice, Luke's rousing anthems and contemplative ballads range from our First Peoples to refugees, fracking, war, drug addiction and some light hearted commentary on modern life. Winner of the 2018 Yackandandah Folk Festival Busking Competition (open section), he will release his debut album later that year.

artists.name: Maja
artists.summary: Captivating her audiences, Serbian-born songstress Maja is making quite a name for herself through her thought provoking and deeply personal song-writing style. Echoing soul, folk and blues music, Maja's diverse range of styles come to highlight her eccentric character and fierce vocal performance.

artists.name: Marcia Howard
artists.summary: Marcia has sustained a diverse career over the past 30 years. She was a member of the legendary Australian band, Goanna as a backing singer, keyboard player and songwriter.  She was named Artist of the Year at PFFF 2016, and appeared on the Voice 2016, in Delta Goodrem's team. She released her 5th album "Everything Reminds Me"

artists.name: Marisa Quigley & Her Sunday Best
artists.summary: Singer-songwriter Marisa Quigley is a fine storyteller and powerful vocalist. Backed by some of the North East's finest musicians, her songs span the gamut from haunting to heartfelt to hilarious. With an eclectic blend of blues/roots, country/folk, a wink and a nudge, a tickle and a poke, their act is soulful, fun and endearing.

artists.name: Melissa Crabtree with Dayan Kai
artists.summary:
Melissa Crabtree is a world traveling, river running, award winning singer/songwriter/guitarist who crafts original music rooted in her love for the wild, majestic lands of the American West.
Dayan Kai  is a classically trained multi-instrumentalist, singer/songwriter, vocalist, and producer with a lifelong dedication to music

artists.name: Monique Clare
artists.summary: Dancing between intricate, rhythmic cello lines, compelling lyrics and heart-tugging harmonies, Monique Clare is an award-winning, song-writing powerhouse. Onstage she's described as a pure joy

artists.name: Montgomery Church
artists.summary: Cielle Montgomery and James Church are "Montgomery Church" - a blend of acoustic folk, americana and bluegrass influences, grown and distilled in the Snowy Mountain ranges of country New South Wales. With their organic union of dobro and guitar, harmony vocals, and tasteful songwriting, this captivating duo are enthralling in their dynamic intimacy and embrace all that is subtle, spacious, and sensitive.

artists.name: Nathan Power
artists.summary: Borrowing inspiration from artists such as the Tallest Man on Earth Bob Dylan and Leonard Cohen Nathan Power explores a love of folk music to communicate stories loosely based on life experiences. Armed with a parlour guitar and backed by mandolin, this is folk music at its finest.

artists.name: Nicky Bomba
artists.summary: Nicky Bomba is an internationally renowned musician, producer and songwriter. As leader of the ARIA award winning Melbourne Ska Orchestra, front man for the Carribean styled Bustamento and highly respected drummer (3 albums with John Butler Trio) he is constantly touring and working on musical adventures. Over the years Nicky has formed and played with bands purely for the love of the music and the adventures they create.  He started playing drums at the tender age of six and, with his future assured, has carved an incredible body of work with no signs of slowing up. With a passion for culture and people, Nicky has travelled extensively, immersing himself in the music and culture. Consequently, the music produced by this peace-lovin’ troubadour is a melting pot of fun, adventure and exotic sounds of the people and places he loves.

artists.name: O'SHEA-RYAN IRISH DANCERS
artists.summary: Performances of Irish Jigs and Reels in Solo and Groups.  Dancers from tiny tots to seniors all dressed in colourful costumes with a Celtic designs, dancing to lively toe tapping Irish Music....delightful displays for audiences.

artists.name: Paige Black
artists.summary: Paige Black is a singer songwriter who will caresse you with her melodic, soulful sound and draw you in with her raw emotion and relatable stories. Paige’s unique voice, backed by the keys, bring you sounds of soul, pop and folk rolled into one. Paige will take you on a journey with her songs narrating the places she’s been, the relationships she’s made and her sense of curiosity.

artists.name: Pans on Fire
artists.summary: The repertoire of the 'Pans on Fire' Steelpan orchestra includes Calypso, Latin, Samba, Bossa, Jazz, world music, rock ballads and classical music. During our show we talk about our bushfire recovery process using the pan, the origine of the steelpan music, how the instrument is made and the variety of sounds one can make with it. We also provide workshops at the end of our shows.

artists.name: Pete Denahy
artists.summary: Having cut his teeth doing comedy and playing fiddle on the Slim Dusty Show, five time Golden Guitar winner Pete works at his own show now which includes much comedy and also features his fine original songs, many of which are from his current bluegrass release, “Singin’ Shoes”- songs inspired by the history of Yackandandah, Vic.,  where he lives .His latest comedy offering, entitled “You Actually Burn More Calories Eating Celery Than You Get From The Celery Itself” is a collection of songs that includes the popular first single "You Actually Burn More Calories Eating Celery Than You Get From The Celery Itself" along with “Toilet Paper”, “Underpants” and “Poker Machine”.

artists.name: Red Tail Ring
artists.summary: Michigan-based, Red Tail Ring are Laurel Premo and Michael Beauchamp. Together they create intricate arrangements of original folk music and traditional ballads with banjo, fiddle, guitar, and lush harmonies. "The very best of the 21st century's minimalist folk music, a peerless duo.“ American Roots UK. Fresh off their fourth full-length studio release, Fall Away Blues, Premo and Beauchamp are "re-imagining Americana music with pure soul" The Steel Wheels.

artists.name: Richard Gilewitz
artists.summary: For nearly four decades, American fingerstyle wizard Richard Gilewitz has fascinated listeners with 6 and 12-string finger gymnastics while spinning enchanting yarns of a seasoned raconteur.His signature playing style delivers a technical diversity of banjo style patterns and classical arpeggios with a rhythmic percussive approach, exploring the history of guitar with sounds of folk to Americana, the blues to the classical, ragtime to pop, and somewhere in between.

artists.name: Rosie Haden and Greg Hoepner
artists.summary: Music to swoon by, Dark electric folk, Grace Slick meets Neko Case,  Melodic,  harmonic, edgy and rhythmic

artists.name: Saoirse
artists.summary: The Saoirse experience! This award winning Celtic band will enthrall any audience with their beautiful songs, luscious harmonies, feisty jigs and reels and fabulous dancing feet. With a selection of traditional tunes and songs and original works  Saoirse are the real Celtic deal!

artists.name: The Frank Burkitt Band
artists.summary: Frank Burkitt is a songwriter and a storyteller who has been performing his own brand of folk song for over 15 years. After relocating from Edinburgh to Wellington he formed an insanely talented backing band that have become popular throughout New Zealand and Australia for their quirky arrangements, up beat performances and sharp suits! American Roots music with flavours of country, jazz and swing.

artists.name: The Go Set
artists.summary: The Go Set combines the traditional sounds of bagpipes, fiddle and mandolin, with rock guitars, and rousing choruses. A hybrid of the old and the new, and a dynamic and engaging live act not to be missed.

artists.name: The Humbuckin’ Pickups
artists.summary: High energy and a love of performing see The Humbuckin’ Pickups produce a show that is captivating and beautiful to witness. It’s Australiana rockin’ folk! The Humbuckers are a fun-loving lot, drawing the crowd in with their stories, their humour and their captivating songs

artists.name: The Jam Tarts Trio
artists.summary: The Jam Tarts Trio are a quirky group of women who celebrate aging well by singing the  music of the 50's and 60's with a touch of theatre, quirky choreography and loads of fun which engages audiences of all ages.<

artists.name: The Maes
artists.summary: The Maes have brought their contemporary twist on folk music on the road across Australia, Canada, USA and Europe with performances at the Hydro Stadium at Celtic Connection, Glasgow, Americana Folk Festival, Nashville, Cambridge Folk Festival, UK; Edmonton Folk Festival, Vancouver Folk Music Festival, Canada; Woodford, Port Fairy and National Folk Festivals, Australia.

artists.name: The Neon Effect
artists.summary: Harpist Michelle Doyle, cellist Catie Martin and oboist/fiddler Jessica Foot meld their rich sonorities with eclectic craftsmanship to explore the far reaches of the contemporary Aussie-Trad musical vernacular. Through soulful strains, deep grooves and an explosion of colour, The Neon Effect ignites the music of their time and place.

artists.name: The Royal High Jinx
artists.summary: Australia's mesmerising contemporary world music band The Royal High Jinx have burst onto festival stages with originality, virtuosity and theatricality. Their songs and tunes are inspired by European traditions peppered with Gypsy Jazz, Latin, Balkan & Electro-Swing grooves with a pinch of Folk. In 2018 TRHJ excited and ignited European audiences on their  "Gone Gone Gone"

artists.name: The Settlement
artists.summary: THE SETTLEMENT are a band of brothers from regional Victoria that rose from the beer-soaked â€œpubâ€

artists.name: Tinman
artists.summary: Born out of a New Year's eve campfire sing-along, Tinman is a group of friends making dreamy folk music infused with the voicings of mandolin, cigar box guitar, piano accordion and ukulele. Add to that the lush vocals and seductive harmonies font-women Richelle and Sarah-Rose, the quartet is a dream combination that come together to create an electric live performance.

artists.name: Tom Richardson
artists.summary: With an infectious and genuine demeanor, Tom's songwriting, story telling and intricate guitar playing are a delicate balance of grace, truth and passion. At a live performance, it's not uncommon to experience people laughing, crying, dancing and singing.  Renowned as a maestro

artists.name: Whitedog
artists.summary: "Whitedog" aka Wayne Robert Davies is an Alternative Country Folk singer and songwriter from the UK. A career that has seen appearances at Earls Court (supporting Van Morisson), touring the UK club circuit with an 8 piece Ska band and appearing at UK festivals including Glastonbury. He is an endearing singer songwriter who engages his audience with jokes and observations.

artists.name: Z-Star Delta
artists.summary: Z-STAR DELTA is an explosive duo fronted by international artist, multi-instrumentalist and producer Zee Gachette (Z-STAR, SLOWTRAINSOUL), based in the UK. Fast becoming hot music property and being hailed as the highlight of many a festival, thanks to their legendary and high octane live performances. The duo have a sound that travels through an intoxicating and modern mix of Country Blues and Desert Rock.

artists.name: Yoga Loves Music
artists.summary: Yoga Loves Music is your new favourite way to experience yoga. Imagine a yoga practice, merged with live music, humour, playfulness and connection. Step into a soulful blend of contemporary live music, weaved with traditional mantras and paired with heart wisdom. A workshop combination of live sound and a yoga practice fuelled on waves of vibrational soundscapes & collective breath, invoking the highest connection to our true essence and awakening of mojo!

artists.name: Matt McIntyre
artists.summary: Matt is the winner of the 2018 Yackoustic Competition

artists.name: Black Orchid Stringband
artists.summary: Black Orchid Stringband comprises of West Papuan musicians based in Melbourne who maintain the spirit of national unity in their freedom struggle through rhythmic ukuleles and big harmonies.

artists.name: Yackandandah Community Choir
artists.summary: When a village with a population of less than 1000 can muster more than 120 to 150 voices to rehearse and perform together for the community's folk festival, it says something about the unique strength and community capacity in Yackandandah. This much loved group has put together a rousing and harmonious repertoire guaranteed to allow you to finish off the festival on a high. All credit to the wonderful choir and the energetic committee. An un-ticketed event; all are welcome to come and share the love as they lift spirits and lift the roof.

artists.name: Tom Yates
artists.summary: Tom drives our festival poets' breakfast , and this year also presents , with laid back guitar , a selection from his repertoire of lyrical and moving songs.

artists.name: Earth Hour
artists.summary: Join us again for Earth Hour at the Public Hall. Once the lights will go out you will be treated to 10 surprise acts, completely acoustic, in the dark.

artists.name: Mezz Coleman
artists.summary:
With a powerful voice imbued with honesty, Melbourne songbird Mezz Coleman writes & sings of love, loss & community. After graduating from VCA with a Bachelor of Music Performance (Jazz Improvisation), Mezz eventually found her home in the folk & indie pop traditions. With her ukulele in hand, she has spent the last decade performing in Melbourne and around regional Victoria, establishing herself
as both a prolific songwriter & engaging performer.
